     <font class="TallRed">To all the gamers and computer geeks here.<a name="109194259317736907">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          Has anyone here played Doom 3 yet? I normally cannot stand most shooters as they are pretty much blow up everything in sight and are mindless. My preference for shooters is usually Splinter Cell, Ghost Recon, Siphon Fliter etc.. When I tried the beta a few months back, I was very disappointed. Now the release version is here and this game is fucking incredible. Id has done a wonderful job of making sure this thing runs well on low end systems and high end systems. Currently I am running an AMD XP+ 2600 overclocked, Nvidia GeForce 5200 with 128mb overclocked in AGP 8X mode, 1gb of PC3200 ram, a Soundblaster Audigy 1, and an 80gb 7200 rpm ATA 133 HDD. Not a big calculator, but not an SGI machine either. The graphics and sound are phenominal! The shadowing and dynamic lighting really bring the game out, and they have exploited many new DX9 features such as visual rippling from heat sources among other things. I am running the game at 1024 res with everything turned on but the antialiasing. Even with the AA off, there is almost no tearing whatsoever. As good as this thing looks, I am half tempted to go get a GeFore 6800 so I can run it in Ultra Mode. I know some of you all just groaned and are screaming ATI at me as we speak, but if you go read the reviews, the Nvidia GPU is kicking the living shit out of the ATI GPU, and the Doom3 engine is looking poised to bump the Quake/Unreal engine for the next few years. Soundwise, it blows me away, ID has apparently gotten together with Creative and EMU and written special standards for EAX2 in the game. There is an unbelievable amount of ambience, reflections, and doppler effects. This game is simply the best thing I have seen come to market in some time. For anyone who complained about the 10 years it took to bring this one back, it was worth the wait. My only complaint with this game is the flashlight, you cannot have the flashlight and a weapon enabled at the same time. The effect of this makes the game harder which isn't so bad. The AI is great also, enemies never stand there and wait for you, if they hear or see your ass 100yds away, they come after you.<br /><br />Forgot to mention, there is a setting in the config file that will allow all characters to have independent shadows. I know your thinking games already do this, but enable it in this game and see what you have been missing. It reminds me of Toca Race Driver 2, where the sun doesn't just cast shadows, it literally reflects off of everything independently. Also, you find things like warped glass in here that also ripples and distorts as you walk by it.<br /><br />
